definition.value: A monocarboxylic acid that is the O-phenyl derivative of glycolic acid. A metabolite of 2-phenoxyethanol, it is used in the manufacture of pharmaceuticals, pesticides, fungicides and dyes.
A 5-ethenyl-1,3-oxazolidine-2-thione that has S-configuration. It is a constituent of a traditional Chinese herbal medicine, Radix isatidis.
A carbamate ester resulting from the formal condensation of both carboxy groups of hexane-1,6-diylbis(methylcarbamic acid) with the hydroxy group of 3-hydroxy-1-methylpyridinium.
A monocarboxylic acid resulting from the formal condensation of the amino group of 1,4'-bipiperidine with carbonic acid.
A bile acid taurine conjugate derived from ursoodeoxycholic acid.
An oxabicycloalkane consisting of p-menthane with an epoxy bridge across positions 1 and 4.
A glycosyloxyflavone that is kaempferol attached to an alpha-L-rhamnosyl residue at position 3 via a glycosidic linkage.
